column1: :has_definition ""An area of tundra which is present in a region subject to alpine conditions."" .

,The area of alpine tundra is a specific type of tundra area and is characterized as an entity that possesses to some extent the quality of being alpine. It is defined as an area of tundra present in a region subject to alpine conditions.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03400002,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""An area of tundra which is present in a region subject to polar conditions."" .

,The area of polar tundra is a type of tundra area and is classified as something that possesses at least some polar qualities. It is defined as an area of tundra which is present in a region subject to polar conditions.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03400003,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""An area density which inheres in snow distributed over an area of a landmass or other substrate.""@en .

,Snow cover is a type of area density and is defined as an area density which inheres in snow distributed over an area of a landmass or other substrate.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03400004,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .

,Heavy snowfall is defined as snowfall that has an increased rate and is the same as something that intersects between snowfall and something that has at least some increased rate. It is a type of snowfall and also a type of something that has at least some increased rate. Additionally, heavy snowfall is exactly synonymous with intense snowfall and has related synonyms including heavy snow and intense snow.",7,True
:has_definition ""An ice mass which is 1) transparent or translucent, 2) rounded, spherically, or cylindrically shaped, and 3) less than 5 milimetres in diameter.""@en

,An ice pellet is a type of ice mass characterized by specific qualities. It is described as being at least partially transparent or translucent, and its shape can either be spherical or cylindrical. The definition of an ice pellet further clarifies it as an ice mass that is 1) transparent or translucent, 2) rounded, spherically, or cylindrically shaped, and 3) less than 5 millimeters in diameter. Furthermore, ice pellet is synonymously related to terms such as grain of ice, ice grain, sleet, and small hail, indicating the different nomenclatures used to describe this form of precipitation.",8,True
:has_definition ""Snowfall which 1) is localized, 2) is convective, and 3) occurs as a result of a cold, dry air mass absorbing heat and moisture as it flows over a lake with warmer waters.""@en

,Lake effect snowfall is a type of snowfall characterized by several key factors. It occurs when a cold, dry air mass moves over warmer lake waters, absorbing heat and moisture which then leads to snowfall. This process involves a material warming process and includes the participation of lakes. Additionally, it involves air masses that have qualities of decreased temperature and dryness. Lake effect snowfall is defined as snowfall that is localized, convective, and occurs as a result of this specific interaction between the air mass and the lake. It is also known by the exact synonyms ""lake effect snow"" and ""lake-effect snow.""",8,True
:has_definition ""A snowstorm during which intense lake-effect snowfall occurs.""@en

,A lake effect snow storm is a type of snowstorm which is characterized by having a part that intersects with lake effect snowfall and an increased rate. It is defined as a snowstorm during which intense lake-effect snowfall occurs. Additionally, ""lake effect snow storm"" is an exact synonym for itself.",4,True
:has_definition ""A snowfall which occurs during springtime and is of low intensity.""@en
,A lambing storm is a type of snowfall, defined as a snowfall that occurs during springtime and is of low intensity. It has exact synonyms including lamb storm, lamb-blasts, and lamb-showers.",5,True
:has_definition ""An object aggregate which is primarily composed of particles of water in liquid, frozen, or partially frozen states.""@en .

,Falling sleet is an object aggregate that is primarily defined as an aggregate composed of particles of water in liquid, frozen, or partially frozen states. This type of aggregate at least participates in processes that include the intersection of the freezing of water into water ice and the thawing process. Moreover, it at least has members such as water droplets, water ice crystals, and sleet pellets. Additionally, falling sleet is broadly synonymous with sleet.",7,True
:has_definition ""Water-based rain which is composed of supercooled water droplets, which freeze on contact with surfaces.""@en .
,Freezing rain is a type of water-based rain, defined as water-based rain composed of supercooled water droplets, which freeze on contact with surfaces.",2,True
:has_definition ""Precipitation which is composed primarily of hail stones.""@en .

,Hail is a type of precipitation that is composed primarily of hailstones. This classification intersects with objects that are aggregates and with entities that have at least some hailstone as a member.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03400012,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""An ice mass which 1) occurs in a ball-shape or irregular lump, 2) has a minimum diameter of 5 millimeters (or 0.2 inches), and 3) is formed within convective clouds.""@en .

,A hail stone is a type of ice mass, which is also a type of entity that derives from something that is at least partially part of a cloud. It is defined as an ice mass that 1) takes the form of a ball shape or an irregular lump, 2) has a minimum diameter of 5 millimeters (or 0.2 inches), and 3) forms within convective clouds.",3,True
:has_definition ""An object aggregate which is composed primarily of snow falling through an atmosphere.""@en .

,Falling snow is an object aggregate and is primarily composed of snow. It is defined as an object aggregate composed primarily of snow falling through an atmosphere. Additionally, falling snow has a broad synonym: snowfall.",4,True
:has_definition ""A hydrological precipitation process during which water falls in both liquid and frozen form.""@en

,Precipitation of sleet, also broadly known as sleet and more precisely referred to as sleet fall, is a type of hydrological precipitation process. It is defined as a hydrological precipitation process during which water falls in both liquid and frozen form.",4,True
:has_definition ""An ice mass which is primarily composed of frozen or mostly frozen raindrops or refrozen partially melted snowflakes.""@en .

,A sleet pellet is a type of ice mass and is also broadly synonymous with sleet. It is defined as an ice mass primarily composed of frozen or mostly frozen raindrops or refrozen partially melted snowflakes. Furthermore, a sleet pellet is a type of entity that is at least composed primarily of a union of raindrops and snow crystals.",4,True
:has_definition ""An environmental zone which is covered or partially covered by ice.""@en .
,The area of ice cover is a type of environmental zone, defined as an environmental zone that is covered or partially covered by ice.",2,True

,The depth of water ice is defined as the depth of some water ice. It is a type of intersection that involves depth and at least one characteristic of some water ice.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03500001,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A park which has been designed for the recreation of children."" .

,A playground is a type of park defined as a park designed for the recreation of children.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03500002,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A park which is owned by a governmental or state entity and which is accessible by its citizenry (i.e. the public)."" .
,A public park is a type of park with a specific definition: it is a park owned by a governmental or state entity and is accessible by its citizenry, meaning the public.",2,True

:has_definition ""A sports facility which has been constructed for sports that require large outdoor spaces and is owned by a governmental or state entity and which is accessible by its citizenry (i.e. the public)."" .

,A public sports field is a type of sports facility with a specific definition. It is a sports facility constructed for sports that require large outdoor spaces. Moreover, it is owned by a governmental or state entity and is accessible by its citizenry, that is, the public.",2,True
:has_definition ""A constructed pavement which is intended for bicycle traffic"" .

,A bike path is a type of constructed pavement that is intended for bicycle traffic.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03500005,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A material entity which has been discarded outside waste management systems by humans or their technologies.""@en

,Anthropogenic litter is a type of material entity that serves the role of waste and is the output of littering. It is defined as a material entity discarded outside waste management systems by humans or their technologies. This concept is broadly synonymous with ""basura antropogénica,"" ""litter,"" and ""rifiuti antropogenici."" Additionally, its exact synonyms are ""anthropogener Abfall"" and ""menschengemachter Abfall.""",9,True
:has_definition ""An anthropogenic environment in which populations of humans have limited acess to affordable and nutritious food."" .

,A food desert is a type of anthropogenic environment that is defined as an anthropogenic environment where populations of humans have limited access to affordable and nutritious food.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03500007,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""An environment in which entities are exposed to either excessive or constant sound."" .

,A noisy environment is categorized as a type of environmental system characterized by a specific quality. It is defined as an environment where entities are exposed to either constant or excessive sound. This classification also extends to being a type of entity that engages in an intersection of processes that at least realizes sound wave energy.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03500008,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""An environment in which humans have a low likelihood of being harmed or killed."" .
,A safe environment for human presence, which is a type of safe environment for living organisms, is defined as an environment in which humans have a low likelihood of being harmed or killed.",2,True
:has_definition ""An environment which includes components which are deemed to be aesthetically pleasing by a population of humans."" .

,An attractive environment is a type of environmental system characterized by a specific quality. It is defined as an environment that includes components which are deemed to be aesthetically pleasing by a population of humans.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03500010,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""An environmental system which is shielded from direct stellar irradiation by material entities.""

,A shady environment is a type of environmental system characterized by a specific quality. It is defined as an environmental system which is shielded from direct stellar irradiation by material entities. Additionally, a shady environment is exactly synonymous with a shaded environment.",3,True
:has_definition ""An environment in which humans are exposed to regularly occurring physical or emotional violence."" .

,A violent environment is a category of environmental system characterized by a specific quality. It is defined as an environment in which humans are regularly exposed to physical or emotional violence.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03500012,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""An acoustic radiation process during which waves that transmit sound energy at frequencies above 20 kHz are emitted by a source."" .

,Ultrasound radiation, which is a type of acoustic radiation, is defined as an acoustic radiation process during which waves that transmit sound energy at frequencies above 20 kHz are emitted by a source.",2,True
:has_definition ""An infrared radiation during which waves with frequencies between 30 THz and 120 THz and with wavelengths between 10 micrometers and 2.5 micrometers are emitted by a source."" .

,Mid-infrared radiation is a type of infrared radiation defined as the emission of waves from a source with frequencies between 30 THz and 120 THz and wavelengths ranging from 10 micrometers to 2.5 micrometers.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03500014,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""An infrared radiation during which waves with frequencies between 120 THz and 400 THz and with wavelengths between 2.5 micrometers and 750 nanometers are emitted by a source."" .

,Near infrared radiation is a type of infrared radiation defined as the infrared radiation during which waves are emitted by a source with frequencies between 120 THz and 400 THz and with wavelengths between 2.5 micrometers and 750 nanometers.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03500015,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""An infrared radiation which consists of waves with frequencies between 300 GHz and 30 THz and with wavelengths between 1 mm and 10 micrometers are emitted by a source."" .

,Far infrared radiation is a type of infrared radiation. It is defined as an infrared radiation which consists of waves with frequencies between 300 GHz and 30 THz and with wavelengths between 1 mm and 10 micrometers, emitted by a source.",2,True
:has_definition ""A merchant vessel which is used to carry passengers, vehicles, or cargo across a body of water.""@en .
,A ferry is a type of merchant vessel defined as a merchant vessel used to carry passengers, vehicles, or cargo across a body of water.",2,True
:has_definition ""An environmental system which is not sheltered.""@en .

,The outdoor environment is defined as an environmental system that is not sheltered.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501102,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""An industrial building made from steel and covered in polyethylene used for plant cultivation.""@en

,A polytunnel is a type of industrial building characterized as an industrial structure made from steel and covered in polyethylene, specifically designed for plant cultivation. It is also known by several exact synonyms, including grow tunnel, high tunnel, hoop greenhouse, hoophouse, and polyhouse.",7,True
:has_definition ""A motor vehicle which is equipped with medical equipment and can be used to transport humans to treatment facilities.""@en .

,An ambulance is a type of motor vehicle that is equipped with medical equipment and can be used to transport humans to treatment facilities.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501104,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A boat which provides short-term residential and entertainment facilities to passengers.""@en .
,A recreational cruise ship is a type of boat that provides short-term residential and entertainment facilities to passengers. It is also broadly synonymous with the term ""cruise ship"".",3,True
:has_definition ""A transport boat which can be hired.""@en
,A merchant vessel is a type of transport boat, which is defined as a transport boat that can be hired. It has exact synonyms including merchant ship, merchantman, and trading vessel.",5,True
:has_definition ""A vehicle which locomotes using rails and consists of a series of connected compartments used to transport passengers or cargo.""@en .

,A train is a type of vehicle defined as a vehicle which locomotes using rails and consists of a series of connected compartments used to transport passengers or cargo.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501108,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A train which is capable of and used for passenger transport.""@en .

,A passenger train is a type of train that is capable of and used for passenger transport.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501109,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A passenger train which runs along an undergroud rail system.""@en

,A subway train is a type of passenger train that is also a part of some rapid transit system. It is defined as a passenger train which operates along an underground rail system. Furthermore, the term subway train is exactly synonymous with subway, tube train, and underground train. Additionally, it has narrow synonyms including London Underground, SkyTrain, Tube, U-Bahn, Underground, and metropolitana.",12,True
:has_definition ""A system which has components that have been constructed to allow the movement of people or goods.""@en .

,A constructed transport system is a type of system defined as a system which has components that have been constructed to allow the movement of people or goods.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501111,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A constructed transport system which is owned by a government or other form of public representation.""@en

,A public transit system is a type of constructed transport system that is considered at least part of public infrastructure and participates in the usage of an environment for community and social services. It is defined as a constructed transport system owned by a government or other form of public representation. Furthermore, the public transit system is exactly synonymous with both public transport and public transportation.",6,True
:has_definition ""A bus which is part of public infrastructure.""@en
,A public bus is a type of bus characterized by its role as part of public infrastructure. It is exactly synonymous with public autobus, public motorbus, public multibus, and public omnibus.",6,True
:has_definition ""A ferry which is owned by a government or other form of public representation.""@en .

,A public ferry is a type of ferry defined as a ferry which is owned by a government or other form of public representation.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501114,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A train which is owned by a government or other form of public representation.""@en .

,A public train is a type of train with the definition of being a train that is owned by a government or another form of public representation.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501115,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A subway train which is owned by a government or other form of public representation.""@en .

,A public subway train is a type of subway train that is defined as a subway train which is owned by a government or other form of public representation.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501116,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A public transit system which is owned by a government or other form of public representation.""@en

,A rapid transit system is a type of public transit system that is defined as a public transit system owned by a government or other form of public representation. It is exactly synonymous with MRT, mass rapid transit, and metro. Additionally, it has narrow synonyms including heavy rail, light rail, and medium-capacity rail.",8,True
:has_definition ""A place where passengers and cargo are exchanged between vehicles or/and between transport modes.""@en

,A transport hub is a type of human construction defined as a place where passengers and cargo are exchanged between vehicles or/and between transport modes. It is also exactly synonymous with the term transport interchange.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501118,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A transport hub which is part of public infrastructure.""@en

,A public transport hub is a type of transport hub and also falls under the category of something that is at least part of some public infrastructure. It is defined as a transport hub which is part of public infrastructure. Additionally, it has an exact synonym: public transport interchange.",4,True
:has_definition ""A research station in which food production and/or agribusinness research is performed.""@en

,An agricultural experimental station is a type of research station defined as a research station where food production and/or agribusiness research is performed. It has several exact synonyms, including AES, ARS, agricultural research station, and research farm.",6,True
:has_definition ""A farm which produces milk or products derived from milk.""@en .

,A dairy farm is a type of farm that is defined as a farm which produces milk or products derived from milk.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501121,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A building part which is a narrow hall or passage in a building with rooms leading off it.""@en

,A building corridor is a type of building part characterized as a narrow hall or passage in a building with rooms leading off it. It is broadly synonymous with both hall and passage and has an exact synonym, hallway.",5,True
:has_definition ""A human construction with extended facilities from which aircraft flight operations take place.""@en .

,An airport is a type of human construction defined as a human construction with extended facilities from which aircraft flight operations take place. It has broad synonyms such as aerodrome and airdrome.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501123,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""An industrial building in an airport where passengers transfer between facilities and vehicles.""@en .

,An airport terminal is a type of industrial building and also a type of entity that constitutes at least part of an airport. It is defined as an industrial building in an airport where passengers transfer between facilities and vehicles.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501124,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""An industrial building which provides travelers with access to airplanes.""@en .

,An airport concourse is a type of industrial building and is part of some airport terminal. It is defined as an industrial building that provides travelers with access to airplanes.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501125,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A room in an airport where en-route passengers can wait between flights..""@en

,An airport transit lounge is a type of room that is part of at least some airport terminals. It is defined as a room in an airport where en-route passengers can wait between flights. Furthermore, ""transit lounge"" is considered a broad synonym for an airport transit lounge, while ""airport transit room"" is an exact synonym.",5,True
:has_definition ""A building which is primarily used for Christian religious activities.""@en

,A church building is a type of building with the definition being a building which is primarily used for Christian religious activities. Additionally, it has exact synonyms including ""church"" and ""church house.""",4,True
,A conference venue is a type of building defined as a building that accommodates conferences. It has the exact synonyms ""conference center"" and ""conference centre.""",4,True

,A conference room is a type of room and is also considered a part of some conference venues. It is defined as a room which accommodates conferences. Moreover, conference room has exact synonyms, including conference hall and meeting room.",5,True
:has_definition ""A human construction in which people are educated.""@en .

,An educational facility is a type of human construction that is defined as a human construction in which people are educated.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501130,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""An institutional building in which students are educated.""@en .

,A school building is a type of educational facility and has the definition of being an institutional building in which students are educated. Additionally, ""school"" is considered a broad synonym for a school building.",3,True
:has_definition ""An institutional building in which university services are performed.""@en

,A university building is a type of institutional building and is also considered a part of some university campus. It is defined as an institutional building in which university services are performed. Moreover, a university building is exactly synonymous with a campus building and a university college building.",5,True
:has_definition ""An institutional building in which firefighting apparati are stored, and which may include staff living spaces.""@en

,A fire station is a type of institutional building which is defined as an institutional building in which firefighting apparatus are stored, and which may include staff living spaces. Additionally, a fire station has several exact synonyms including engine house, fire hall, fire house, and firemen's hall.",6,True
:has_definition ""An institutional building which temporarily houses homeless people.""@en .

,A homeless shelter is defined as an institutional building that temporarily houses homeless people and is a type of institutional building.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501134,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A human construction in which healthcare is provided.""@en

,A healthcare facility is a type of human construction defined as a human construction in which healthcare is provided. This healthcare facility is also exactly synonymous with both a health facility and a medical facility.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501135,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A healthcare facility which is used for short-term patient care.""@en
,An acute care facility is a type of healthcare facility known for providing short-term patient care. This type of facility is also precisely referred to as ACC, ACF, or an acute care center.",5,True
:has_definition ""A healthcare facility in which patients are medically assessed.""@en

,A clinical patient assessment facility is a type of healthcare facility that is defined as a healthcare facility in which patients are medically assessed. It is broadly synonymous with CAC and clinical assessment centre. Additionally, it has exact synonyms such as clinical patient assessment center and clinical patient assessment centre.",6,True
:has_definition ""A healthcare facility which 1) is located in part of a hospital and 2) is used by an organizational unit within a hospital.""@en

,A hospital unit facility is a type of healthcare facility and also a type of entity that is at least partly located within some hospital. It is defined as a healthcare facility which is 1) located in part of a hospital and 2) is used by an organizational unit within a hospital. Additionally, it has an exact synonym, ""hospital ward.""",4,True
:has_definition ""A hospital unit facility which is used for anaesthetic service provision.""@en

,The anaesthetics unit facility is a type of hospital unit facility characterized by its use for anaesthetic service provision. It is exactly synonymous with both anaesthesia unit and anaesthesia ward.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501139,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A hospital unit facility which is used for breast cancer screening.""@en

,A breast screening unit facility is a type of hospital unit facility designed for breast cancer screening. It is also known by several exact synonyms, including breast assessment unit, breast screening ward, and mammography unit.",5,True
:has_definition ""A hospital unit facility which is used to provide nondemoninational religious services.""@en

,A chaplaincy unit facility is a type of hospital unit facility that is used to provide nondemoninational religious services. It is also known exactly as a chaplain unit and chaplain's unit.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501141,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A hospital unit facility which is used to provide cardiac patient care.""@en

,A coronary care unit facility is a type of hospital unit facility designed to provide cardiac patient care. It is also known by several exact synonyms including CCU, CCW, CICU, cardiac care unit, coronary care ward, cardiac intensive care ward, and cardiac intensive care unit.",9,True
:has_definition ""A hospital unit facility which is used to provide diagnostic imaging services.""@en

,The diagnostic imaging unit facility is a type of hospital unit facility specifically used to provide diagnostic imaging services. It is also exactly synonymous with diagnostic imaging ward, medical imaging unit, and medical imaging ward.",5,True
:has_definition ""A hospital unit facility which houses patients ready to leave the hospital facility.""@en

,A discharge unit facility is a type of hospital unit facility characterized by being a hospital unit facility that houses patients ready to leave the hospital facility. This facility is also precisely known as a discharge lounge and a discharge ward.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501144,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A hospital unit facility which is used to provide emergency medicine services.""@en

,The emergency unit facility is a type of hospital unit facility that is used to provide emergency medicine services. It has several exact synonyms, including A&E, ED, ER, EW, accident & emergency department, casualty department, emergency department, emergency room, and emergency ward.",11,True
:has_definition ""A room in which emergency medical care is provided.""@en

,An emergency unit room is a type of room that is at least partially situated within some emergency unit facility. It is defined as a room in which emergency medical care is provided. This room is also exactly synonymous with several terms including A&E room, ER room, EW room, accident & emergency department room, casualty department room, emergency department room, emergency room, and emergency ward room.",11,True
:has_definition ""A hospital unit facility which is used to provide gastroenterology medical services.""@en .

,The gastroenterology unit facility is a type of hospital unit facility designed to provide gastroenterology medical services.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501147,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A hospital unit facility which is used to provide surgical services.""@en

,The general surgery unit facility is a type of hospital unit facility defined as a hospital unit facility used to provide surgical services. It is also exactly synonymous with several terms, including general surgery ward, general surgical unit, general surgical ward, surgery unit, surgery ward, surgical unit, and surgical ward.",9,True
:has_definition ""A hospital unit facility which is used to provide geriatric medical services.""@en

,The geriatric care unit facility is a type of hospital unit facility designed to provide geriatric medical services. It is also known by several exact synonyms, including elderly unit, geriatric care ward, geriatric unit, and geriatric ward.",6,True
:has_definition ""An intensive care unit facility which is used to provide care of critically ill elderly patients.""@en

,The Geriatric Intensive Care Unit Facility is a type of Intensive Care Unit Facility specifically used to provide care for critically ill elderly patients. It is exactly synonymous with both GICU and Geriatric Intensive Care Ward.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501150,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A hospital unit facility which is used to provide gynaecologic medical services.""@en

,The gynaecology unit facility is a type of hospital unit facility that is used to provide gynecologic medical services. It is also exactly synonymous with the term gynaecology ward.,3,True

,Motor oil is a type of manufactured product that serves as a lubricant for internal combustion engines. Additionally, motor oil is also known by its exact synonyms: engine lubricant and engine oil.",4,True
:has_definition ""A liquid fuel used in diesel engines, whose fuel ignition takes place, without any spark, as a result of compression of the inlet air mixture and then injection of fuel."" .

:has_definition ""A gas which results from the incomplete or complete combustion of diesel fuel."" .

,Diesel exhaust is defined as a gas which results from the incomplete or complete combustion of diesel fuel and is a type of gaseous environmental material that originates from diesel fuel. It comprises a complex mixture of substances including acrolein, water, ammonia, hydrogen sulfide, methane, carbon dioxide, benzene, formaldehyde, carbon monoxide, toluene, methanol, hydrogen cyanide, sulfur dioxide, inorganic sulfate salt, iron molecular entity, nitrous acid, sulfuric acid, zinc molecular entity, formic acid, elemental carbon, lead molecular entity, polycyclic hydrocarbon, platinum molecular entity, nitrogen oxide, barium molecular entity, buta 1,3-diene, nitric acid, inorganic nitrate salt, heterocyclic compound, and particulate environmental material. This composition highlights the complex nature of diesel exhaust and its potential impact on the environment.",33,True
:has_definition ""A gas which results from the complete or incomplete combustion of gasoline fuel."" .

:has_definition ""An environmental material which is composed of elastic polymers mixed in a solvent.""@en

,Rubber cement is a manufactured product that falls under the category of anthropogenic and hydrocarbon-based environmental materials. :has_definition ""An environmental material which is 1) composed primarily of methyl cellulose and water, and 2) formulated to fix wallpaper to walls.""@en

,Permanent hair dye is a manufactured product and an anthropogenic environmental material. :has_definition ""A soil surface which is exposed to the troposphere, with no appreciable cover from vegetation or other material."" .

:has_definition ""Particulate environmental material which is composed primarily of organic material."" .

,Particulate organic matter is a type of particulate environmental material and something that is at least composed primarily of some organic material. It is defined as particulate environmental material which is composed primarily of organic material.,3,True

:has_definition ""Particulate organic matter which is composed primarily of carbon."" .

,Particulate organic carbon is a type of particulate organic matter and is also a type of entity that is at least composed primarily of some carbon group molecular entity. It is defined as particulate organic matter which is composed primarily of carbon.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_04000014,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""Particulate organic matter which is composed primarily of nitrogen."" .

,Particulate organic nitrogen is a type of particulate organic matter and something that is composed primarily of some nitrogen molecular entity. It is defined as particulate organic matter which is composed primarily of nitrogen.,3,True

:has_definition ""A material accumulation process during which atmospheric carbon dioxide is captured and stored."" .

,The carbon sequestration process is identical to a process that is at the intersection of material accumulation processes and processes that involve atmospheric carbon dioxide as a participant. It is classified as a type of material accumulation process and also as a type that involves atmospheric carbon dioxide. Furthermore, it is defined as a material accumulation process during which atmospheric carbon dioxide is captured and stored.",4,True
:has_definition ""A carbon sequestration process during which atmospheric carbon dioxide is captured and stored by biological processes."" .

,Biotic carbon sequestration is a type of carbon sequestration process and is also a type of something that at least has some part of a biological process. It is defined as a carbon sequestration process during which atmospheric carbon dioxide is captured and stored by biological processes.,3,True

:has_definition ""A carbon sequestration process during which carbon dioxide is stored in underground geological formations.""

,Geological carbon sequestration is a type of carbon sequestration process that involves the storage of carbon dioxide in underground geological formations. This process, which has at least one participant being some subsurface landform, is defined as a carbon sequestration process during which carbon dioxide is stored in underground geological formations. Additionally, geological carbon sequestration is related to abiotic carbon sequestration through a synonym relationship.",4,True
:has_definition ""A carbon sequestration process during which carbon dioxide is stored in the carbonate system of an ocean."" .

,Carbon sequestration by the ocean carbonate system is a type of carbon sequestration process that occurs in some oceans and involves the carbonate system of ocean water as a participant. It is defined as a carbon sequestration process during which carbon dioxide is stored in the carbonate system of an ocean.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_06105002,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A disposition inhering in a bearer by virtue of that bearer's ability to, repeatedly, become plastic on heating and harden again on cooling.""@en

,Thermoplasticity is a type of disposition and is defined as a disposition inhering in a bearer by virtue of that bearer's ability to repeatedly become plastic on heating and harden again on cooling. Thermoplasticity also has exact synonyms, including ""termoplasticità"" and ""熱塑性"".",4,True
:has_definition ""An environmental material which is capable of, repeatedly, becoming plastic when heated and hardening again when cooled.""@en .

,Thermoplastic material is a type of environmental material that is defined as an environmental material capable of repeatedly becoming plastic when heated and hardening again when cooled.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_06105004,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

,Thermosetting disposition is a type of disposition characterized by its inherent quality in materials to become rigid when cured by heating. It is also exactly synonymous with 熱固性.,3,True

:has_definition ""A polymer which has been irreversibly hardened by heat-induced curing.""@en

,A thermoset polymer is a type of polymer defined as a polymer that has been irreversibly hardened by heat-induced curing. It is broadly synonymous with thermoset material and has exact synonyms such as thermoset and thermoset plastic.,5,True

:has_definition ""A piece of plastic which has a matrix- or sponge-like structure with numerous, hollow internal spaces.""@en

,A piece of plastic foam is a type of piece of plastic that is defined as a piece of plastic which has a matrix- or sponge-like structure with numerous, hollow internal spaces. Additionally, it possesses exact synonyms, including Plastikschaumstück and Schaumstoffstück.",4,True
:has_definition ""A piece of plastic which is flexible, thin, and planar.""@en

,Plastic film is a type of piece of plastic that is defined as a piece of plastic which is flexible, thin, and planar. It has exact synonyms such as Plastikfolie, pellicola di plastica, and película de plástico. Additionally, plastic film has a narrow synonym, Kunststofffolie, and related synonyms including plastic membrane and plastic sheet.",8,True
:has_definition ""A piece of plastic which 1) is hard, 2) has an irregular shape, and 3) has broken off of a larger piece of plastic.""@en

,A plastic fragment is a type of piece of plastic that is defined as a piece of plastic which is hard, has an irregular shape, and has broken off of a larger piece of plastic. :has_definition ""A piece of plastic which is linear and flexible.""@en
,A plastic line is a type of piece of plastic, defined as a piece of plastic that is linear and flexible. It has exact synonyms including plastic fibre, plastic filament, and plastic strand.",5,True
:has_definition ""A piece of plastic which is 1) hard, 2) has a smooth external surface, and 3) has a roughly spherical or granular shape.""@en

,A plastic pellet is a type of piece of plastic defined as a piece of plastic that is hard, has a smooth external surface, and has a roughly spherical or granular shape. :has_definition ""A liquid astronomical body part which 1) vertically spans a water body and 2) has fiat boundaries approximating a columnar shape.""@en

,A water column is a type of liquid astronomical body part defined as a liquid astronomical body part that vertically spans a water body and has fiat boundaries approximating a columnar shape. It has several exact synonyms including Wassersäule, colonna d'acqua, columna de agua, and 水層.",6,True
:has_definition ""A collection of organisms which inhabits the same region, ecosystem, or time period.""@en

,Biota refers to a collection of organisms that inhabit the same region, ecosystem, or time period. It is defined as a collection of organisms which inhabits the same region, ecosystem, or time period. The exact synonyms for biota include Biota and biota.",5,True
:has_definition ""A biota which inhabits a marine ecosystem.""@en

,Marine biota is a type of biota that is defined as a biota which inhabits a marine ecosystem. It has several exact synonyms including Meeresbiota, biota marino, marine life, ocean life, and sea life.",8,True
:has_definition ""A biological process during which a material entity is broken down.""@en

,Biodegradation is a type of biological process characterized by the breakdown of a material entity. It is defined as a biological process during which a material entity is broken down. Biodegradation is also known by several exact synonyms, including Biodegradation itself, Biologischer Abbauprozess, biodegradación, biodegradazione, and 生物分解.",7,True
:has_definition ""A biodegradation process during which plastic is broken down.""@en

,Biodegradation of plastic is a type of biodegradation and is defined as a biodegradation process during which plastic is broken down. It is exactly synonymous with ""Biologischer Plastikabbauprozess,"" ""biodegradación del plástico,"" ""biodegradazione della plastica,"" and ""biological degradation of plastics.""",6,True
:has_definition ""A plastic which has a matrix- or sponge-like structure with numerous, hollow internal spaces.""@en

,Foamed plastic is a type of plastic that is characterized by a matrix- or sponge-like structure with numerous, hollow internal spaces. It is broadly synonymous with cellular polymers and expanded polymers, and it is exactly synonymous with geschäumter Kunststoff and plastic foam.",6,True
:has_definition ""A physical quality which inheres in a liquid or solid bearer by virtue of that bearer trapping a gas in a colloidal suspension throughout its volume.""@en .

,The quality of a foam is categorized as a type of physical quality, defined as a physical quality that inheres in a liquid or solid bearer by virtue of that bearer trapping a gas in a colloidal suspension throughout its volume.",2,True
:has_definition ""A feeding behavior during which material is taken into the body of an organism.""@en

,Ingestion is a type of eating behavior and is defined as a feeding behavior during which material is taken into the body of an organism. It has exact synonyms including ""(Nahrungs)aufnahme,"" ""Ingestion,"" ""ingestione,"" ""ingestión,"" and ""攝食.""",7,True
:has_definition ""A material accumulation process during which material adheres to a solid or liquid surface.""@en

,Adsorption is a type of material accumulation process, which is defined as a material accumulation process during which material adheres to a solid or liquid surface. It has exact synonyms including Adsorption, adsorbimento, adsorción, and 吸附.",6,True
:has_definition ""A material accumulation process during which material builds up on a solid surface such that a function of that surface, or the object it is a part of, is impaired.""@en

,Fouling is a type of material accumulation process and is defined as a material accumulation process during which material builds up on a solid surface such that a function of that surface, or the object it is part of, is impaired. Furthermore, fouling has the exact synonyms ""Fouling,"" ""incrostazione,"" and ""incrustación.""",5,True
:has_definition ""A fouling process during which biological matter accumulates on a solid surface.""@en

,Biofouling is a type of fouling defined as a fouling process during which biological matter accumulates on a solid surface. It is also relatedly synonymous with Bewuchs.",8,True
:has_definition ""An environmental system process during which two dissimilar materials attach to one another.""@en .
,Adhesion is a type of environmental system process quality, defined as an environmental system process during which two dissimilar materials attach to one another.",2,True

:has_definition ""An environmental system process during which the molecules of similar materials are electrically attracted to one another, leading to the formation and maintenance of a microscopic structure holding the materials together.""@en .

,Cohesion is a quality of an environmental system process characterized by the electrical attraction between molecules of similar materials. This process results in the formation and maintenance of a microscopic structure that holds the materials together, defining cohesion as an environmental system process during which this specific type of attraction occurs.",2,True
:has_definition ""A piece of plastic foam which has a near-spherical or granular shape.""@en .
,A granule of plastic foam is defined as a piece of plastic foam that possesses a near-spherical or granular shape, indicating that it is a specific type of piece of plastic foam.",2,True
:has_definition ""An environmental system process during which a material entity breaks into pieces or parts.""@en

:has_definition ""A fragmentation process which is caused by weathering.""@en .
,Fragmentation due to weathering is a type of fragmentation process, defined as a fragmentation process caused by weathering.",2,True
:has_definition ""An environnmental material which 1) is composed primarily of polymers with high molecular mass and 2) once deformed does not spontaneously return to its original shape.""@en

,Plastic is recognized as an environmental material characterized by its composition, primarily consisting of polymers with high molecular mass, and its behavior, where it does not spontaneously return to its original shape once deformed. This material is alternatively known as Plastik, plastica, and 塑膠, each term serving as an exact synonym for plastic. Additionally, plastic has a narrow synonym, Kunststoff, indicating a more specific or limited association compared to its exact synonyms.",6,True
:has_definition ""A piece of plastic which is greater than 1 metre in its longest dimension.""@en .

:has_definition ""A piece of plastic which is between 25 and 1000 millimetres in its longest dimension.""@en .
,A macroplastic particle is a type of piece of plastic, defined as a piece of plastic which is between 25 and 1000 millimeters in its longest dimension.",2,True
:has_definition ""A piece of plastic which is between 5 and 25 millimetres in its longest dimension.""@en .

,A mesoplastic particle is a type of piece of plastic defined as a piece of plastic which is between 5 and 25 millimeters in its longest dimension.,2,True

It is also exactly known as Plastiksphäre and plastisfera.",5,True
:has_definition ""Anthropogenic litter which is present in the marine environment.""@en

,Marine anthropogenic litter is a type of anthropogenic litter that is part of, at least to some extent, the marine environment. It is defined as anthropogenic litter which is present in the marine environment. Additionally, it has the exact synonym 海洋廢棄物.",4,True
:has_definition ""An anthropogenic environmental process during which waste is improperly disposed of into the environment.""@en .

,Littering is a type of anthropogenic environmental process and is defined as an anthropogenic environmental process during which waste is improperly disposed of into the environment. Additionally, it is a type of process that at least outputs some anthropogenic litter.",3,True

,A manufactured plastisphere, which is defined as a plastisphere composed primarily of manufactured plastic, is a type of plastisphere.",2,True
:has_definition ""Plastic which is composed primarily of polymers produced by processes whose agents do not include humans or their technologies.""@en .

,Natural plastic is a type of plastic that is at least partially formed as a result of the union of environmental system processes and biological processes. It is also defined as a type of material that, to some extent, forms as a result of processes that are not part of manufacturing processes. Moreover, natural plastic is defined as plastic which is composed primarily of polymers produced by processes whose agents do not include humans or their technologies.",4,True
:has_definition ""A plastic which is composed primarily of polymers produced by a manufacturing process.""@en

,Synthetic plastic, which is a type of plastic, is defined as a plastic primarily composed of polymers produced by a manufacturing process. It is also exactly synonymous with manufactured plastic.",3,True
:has_definition ""A planned environmental usage process during which any number of fish are caught by humans or their technologies.""@en

,Fishing is described as a planned environmental usage process where any number of fish are caught by humans or their technologies. It is defined as a process during which fish are captured. Additionally, fishing is exactly synonymous with several terms including ""angeln,"" ""fischen,"" and ""pesca.""",6,True
:has_definition ""An anthropogenic environmental process during which abandoned, lost, or discarded fishing gear attracts and entangles organisms.""@en .

:has_definition ""A manufactured product which is used for fishing.""@en

,Fishing gear is defined as a manufactured product used for fishing and is a type of product that is at least involved in some fishing activities. It has several exact synonyms, including ""Angelausrüstung,"" ""Angelzubehör,"" ""Fischereiausrüstung,"" ""attrezzo di pesca,"" ""equipo de pesca,"" ""fishing tackle,"" and ""漁具.""",10,True
:has_definition ""Abandoned fishing gear which was intentionally left unmaintained and uncontrolled by its custodian.""@en

,Discarded fishing gear is a type of abandoned fishing gear, defined as abandoned fishing gear that was intentionally left unmaintained and uncontrolled by its custodian. It is broadly synonymous with ""entsorgte Angelausrüstung"" and ""equipo de pesca desechado."" Moreover, it has exact synonyms including ""attrezzo di pesca scartato,"" ""weggeworfene Angelausrüstung,"" ""weggeworfene Fischerreiausrüstung,"" and ""weggeworfenes Angelzubehör.""",8,True
:has_definition ""Fishing gear which is not under the control of or maintained by its custodian.""@en .
,Abandoned fishing gear, which is defined as fishing gear not under the control of or maintained by its custodian, is a type of fishing gear.",2,True
:has_definition ""Abandoned fishing gear which was unintentionally left unmaintained and uncontrolled by its custodian.""@en

,Lost fishing gear, defined as abandoned fishing gear which was unintentionally left unmaintained and uncontrolled by its custodian, is a type of abandoned fishing gear. This lost fishing gear is exactly synonymous with ""attrezzo di pesca perso,"" ""equipo de pesca perdido,"" and ""verschollene Angelausrüstung.""",5,True
:has_definition ""A material transformation process during which the properties of a material are changed as a result of in situ exposure to atmospheric processes.""@en

,Weathering is a type of material transformation process, defined as a material transformation process during which the properties of a material are changed as a result of in situ exposure to atmospheric processes. It is also exactly synonymous with ""Verwitterung,"" ""meteorización,"" ""meteorizzazione,"" and ""風化(作用).""",6,True
:has_definition ""An environmental system process during which material entities become entrapped, wrapped, twisted, entwined, or otherwise caught in one another.""@en

,The entanglement process is a type of environmental system process that is also categorized under processes that output entities at the intersection of material entities and entities that possess the quality of being tangled. It is defined as an environmental system process during which material entities become entrapped, wrapped, twisted, entwined, or otherwise caught in one another. This process goes by several synonyms
column2: broadly, it is known as Verfangen, Verhedderung, and Verstrickung. In terms of exact synonyms, it is referred to as ""proceso de enredamiento"" and ""processo di impigliamento.""",8,True

column1: :has_definition ""An entanglement process during which organisms become entrapped in anthropogenic marine debris.""@en .

,Entanglement of organisms in marine debris is identified as a specific type of entanglement process. This process is characterized by involving anthropogenic litter and organisms as its inputs. Additionally, it results in an output that is an intersection of an organism and a state that possesses the quality of being tangled. Furthermore, the entanglement of organisms in marine debris is defined as an entanglement process during which organisms become entrapped in anthropogenic marine debris.",5,True
:has_definition ""A polymer which is the output of a biological process.""@en .

,A biopolymer is a type of polymer which is defined as a polymer that is the output of a biological process.,2,True
